project: The society you know as the United States has fully collapsed. Excessive student loans caused an abrupt crash in the economy and much of mass media was wiped out in the process.
Food and water began to run low, and eventually the citizens of what once was a known superpower began to depend on the necessities, girl scout cookies.

You are a girl scout from Troop 144. You wear your sash with pride, as you travel across the country to reach Canada in the hopes of finding civilization and escaping the dangerous remains of the west coast.

In order to make it to Canada, you need to pay your ride! You can pay your ride using electricity and water bottles, but you need to either find them or trade cookies for them with people you run into. To move around, use the arrow keys.
To jump, try pressing up on the arrow keys. If you want to trade cookies, press the spacebar when approaching another person. Be careful, if you run out of cookies you’ll have to start all over!
You'll need to collect 4 Water and 4 Electricity to move on, but try to get all you can in each level. You might need it later!
Touching this sign will move you to the next level, provided you have enough resources to pay for travel.
Watch out for Rival Girl Scouts! They'll try to steal your cookies. You can bribe them to leave or just avoid them completely.
Watch out for rival Girl Scouts! They'll steal your Cookies!
If your 'Cookies' drops below 0, you'll have to restart the level.
Make sure to be collecting 'Water' and 'Electricity'. You'll need them to travel.
You're almost there, you'll just need to cross this final level!
You made it to Canada! A refuge where Girl Scouts and humans can live together peacefully. Now go on and live your college-debt free best life.
